document.title: Model School Library Standards for California Public Schools, Kindergarten Through Grade Twelve

67FEA7B8628F4A59BC04843EA0CCAF4B.description: Listen to, view, and read stories, poems, and plays.

C97E904C29504441A3ADD0DC2666250B.description: Appreciate and respond to creative expressions of information:

E842FBCB19A44EC681B03925DE901634.description: Select appropriate information technology tools and resources to interact with others for a specific purpose.

8C08AD4ACF334F87A4E87105C43C3CDA.description: Deliver brief recitations and oral presentations about familiar experiences or interests.

C4CBD93E5ABC4D82B5620106FBB62A3E.description: Read a good representation of grade-level-appropriate text, making progress toward the goal of reading 500,000 words annually by grade four (e.g., classic and contemporary literature, magazines, newspapers, online information).

26D63CFEEFCE4536A1CD88E2C327E9A3.description: Read widely and use various media for information, personal interest, and lifelong learning:

5902259E11E44E4F8E8DF3532ECB45AE.description: Students integrate information literacy skills into all areas of learning.

25593DD634EA4E5F9026D0F506A016D7.description: Use digital or graphic tools to support a presentation.

35CC6E9EA1A34068AFF1840C02A082E5.description: Organize information chronologically, sequentially, or by topic.

A748EC47DD564E17B1680C89D37F49E7.description: Use information and technology creatively to answer a question, solve a problem, or enrich understanding:

6F52D0D9F87548CEB241DB9DFD775C70.description: Compare information from more than one source to draw a conclusion.

211E2EB987494BBDBF29F2BBC611E69D.description: Draw conclusions and make informed decisions:

07BF158926334F2289717ACFC5C9F4F7.description: Identify types of personal information and appropriate and inappropriate ways to share it.

6FCC32D4937E4D83ABDF45E929535067.description: Demonstrate ethical, legal, and safe use of information in print, media, and online resources:

43071DBDD5C6440DBA29F70800350437.description: Locate facts and details to support a topic sentence and paragraph, and record the information.

A0CB9CD2EF0C4A3E9E6D4596FB92FD38.description: Consider the need for additional information:

3BA2443DC20D4A0DA9CAFD402E56ABF9.description: Understand the role and responsibility of the author and publisher to determine accuracy of published materials.

0310116019CB430883B0441C0F9D3A03.description: Identify copyright and publication dates in print resources.

54AB2F04463244AD9CE3BF557246124B.description: Assess the comprehensiveness, currency, credibility, authority, and accuracy of resources:

CF39B0B34F72428D97D251DDE220A727.description: Determine whether the information answers the question.

31BBB4869FE74B8A89751883F156DBCA.description: Select information appropriate to the problem or question at hand.

62CF80D363DD46A68FAC9D2EB03CC10D.description: Determine the relevance of the information:

DE83A5AADCA04F2D95779C58AB361767.description: Apply techniques for organizing notes in a logical order (e.g., outlining, webbing, thinking maps, other graphic organizers).

6866DFC2E72A4F1AA8969D0129CB2778.description: Demonstrate respectful and responsible behavior in the library.

F0AEED027E594FF4B481B390BA7F8089.description: Demonstrate a basic understanding of intellectual property rights and the difference between sharing and ownership.

13BEAFE026D646C48FA1506EDB0B960A.description: Retrieve information in a timely, safe, and responsible manner:

F75D05DE1795413CA7E2A8E5434C5759.description: Locate information in text by using the organizational parts of a book in print or digital format (e.g., title, table of contents, chapter headings, glossary, author notes, dedication, index).

CAF28D31D9E0474CAAEC0915299DB3DB.description: Locate and know the arrangement and general content of the biography section in the library.

B1E952219A7240ABA77167167D8440F3.description: Use print or digital indexes, or both, to locate articles in an encyclopedia.

70A9CB10B2A64AD083C2949F5A130FC9.description: Use specialized content-area print and digital resources to locate information.

857AF2FC075C45F98215D5AC78FDA780.description: Understand the organization of general reference resources in print and/or digital formats, including a dictionary, thesaurus, atlas, almanac, and encyclopedia.

C8B6A3743A79435CBD791F25AAE00639.description: Perform a key word search of a topic by using an approved search engine or database.

DD0EC59C17684445AA08DDFF8821CBDE.description: Use guide words to locate information in a reference book.

A53512ACF05A4E4489609EF5196653D5.description: Identify types of media and digital delivery devices.

4AACF066D7F741D38491D551DBF6E5A1.description: Independently browse the library to locate materials.

E3971175D1194B818CB8F87E9DCC3BF3.description: Understand different systems of alphabetizing (e.g., letter by letter, word by word).

544CE727BCB746F38E6AD7CFD369C189.description: Understand the information on spine labels, including call numbers.

2CBEBD1DFCD64AA48010F3DBF6BC3735.description: Understand that nonfiction print and nonprint materials in a library are arranged by subject (e.g., Dewey decimal system).

3B04EE7E23D24502804358ABFC75833A.description: Perform a basic search of the automated library catalog by title, author, subject, and key word.

B204DC4E078247DEB5D8D551A809BA2F.description: Understand the general purpose of the library catalog.

D13C2A12B95D4C469ED465E644258F63.description: Differentiate between primary and secondary sources.

DCB024EBA2AF4E13AB8429C5037E922A.description: Understand that the function of a library is to provide shared resources that are organized to be accessible to all library users.

9F9636B1EB234A4AA81A17E87B79E8DA.description: Identify and locate a variety of resources online and in other formats by using effective search strategies:

B0337B883E6A4F7094CF29DEE47202A8.description: Identify a problem that needs information by asking how, what, where, when, or why questions.
